EDIT: 'There is alot that can be achieve with communication... wich Taino isnt to good at.. he prefers to flame before knowing the facts..'<br>
<br>
If it happens that 2 guilds raid the same place the same day, there should be communication between those guilds so they can straighten it out in peace.<br>
However, this board is here that exactly this won't be needed. <br>
Normally you check this board, see whether another guild hits your zone the same day. If not, you post your own raid.<br>
When I see VC posting the same raid at the same time, I am not pleased, but we can talk it out and see what we can do, beforehand.<br>
But then a third guild posts their presence in the zone the same day.<br>
Come on, this forum is not here to simply see how many guilds we can fit in one zone. This board is here so we do NOT hit the same zone the same day.<br>
However you turn it around, 3 guilds in one zone will not work out. It will take so much planning, talk, time checks, agreements to figure out who can raid where and when, its silly.<br>
If you see another guild going to the place you wanted to hit, you should simply reschedule it.<br>
<br>
Yes, communication is good. But 3 guilds in one plane at the same day means trouble. WHoever you turn it and how good you may talk. It means trouble and it confuses, in any way. This is why I think it will do no good.<br>
<br>
However, as I mentioned before. I apologize for the harsh language as I was wrong. I won't hide from it, sorry about that.<br>
